### workflow ###
The user wants to perform DNA synthesis. First, I use the Literature agent to search for relevant information on how to perform this experiment. Then, based on the information I get, I use the Protocol agent to generate a possible procedure for the experiment. After that, I use the Reagent agent to check the availability of the reagents required in the procedure. Then, I use the Protocol agent again to generate a validated procedure that is doable with the available reagents. After getting the validated procedure, I use the Code agent to generate the python code for the procedure and run the code using the Hardware agent. The experiment is successfully executed, and I will output the final result.
